.SH NAME
bb-pr-comment-reopen - Reopen a pull request comment thread


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBbb pr comment reopen  [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Reopen a previously resolved pull request comment thread. Accepts a Bitbucket pull request comment URL directly, or a numeric comment ID together with --pr \&.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for reopen

.PP
\fB--host\fP=""
	Bitbucket host to use

.PP
\fB--jq\fP=""
	Filter JSON output using a jq expression

.PP
\fB--json\fP[=""]
	Output JSON with the specified comma-separated fields, or '*' for all fields

.PP
\fB--pr\fP=""
	Parent pull request as an ID or Bitbucket pull request URL; required when the comment target is a numeric ID

.PP
\fB--repo\fP=""
	Bitbucket repository target as , /, or a repository URL

.PP
\fB--workspace\fP=""
	Optional workspace slug used only to disambiguate a bare repository target


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--no-prompt\fP[=false]
	Do not prompt for missing input, even in an interactive terminal


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  bb pr comment reopen https://bitbucket.org/workspace-slug/repo-slug/pull-requests/1#comment-15
  bb pr comment reopen 15 --pr 1 --repo workspace-slug/repo-slug --json '*'
  bb pr comment reopen 15 --pr https://bitbucket.org/workspace-slug/repo-slug/pull-requests/1
.EE


